author: CNN
description: The government has been shutdown for one month, and more than 1 million federal employees are going unpaid, even if they are continuing to work. With no deal in sight, these workers are scared for the future.
title: 'My emergency fund is gone': Federal workers struggling as shutdown drags on

author: CNN
description:
Hurricane Melissa hit Jamaica yesterday as one of the strongest Atlantic hurricanes on record, caused major damage to public infrastructure and left most of the island without power. The full extent of the devastation is unclear with some areas inaccessible.

CNN meteorologist Derek Van Dam reports from an aid convoy in St. Elizabeth Parish, Jamaica, and Jake Tapper speaks with Jamaican information minister Dana Morris Dixon.

For more information about how you can help Hurricane Melissa victims, go to cnn.com/impact #CNN #News
title: Information minister: 'We're completely devastated in Jamaica'

author: CNN
description: An irate Majority Leader John Thune erupted at Democratic Sen. Ben Ray Luján on the Senate floor as frustrations continue to mount amid the government shutdown.
title: Thune erupts on Senate floor as frustrations mount over shutdown

author: CNN
description: CNN's Bill Weir reports on the state of Yosemite National Park after DOGE cuts and the government shutdown decimated the park's staff.
title: Video shows crowded chaos in Yosemite after budget cuts

author: CNN
description: The US Navy’s Blue Angels roared over Washington, DC, on Tuesday morning, a demonstration the Pentagon attributed to an ongoing documentary project and required proficiency training for the pilots. It’s unclear if the funding for the flight was already allocated before the government shutdown began.
title: US Navy's Blue Angels fly over DC

author: CNN
description:
Bill Gates has long devoted a huge amount of time and money to climate change awareness. He now argues more resources should be focused on poverty and hunger, saying that he doesn't think climate change will end humanity. 

CNN chief data analyst Harry Enten breaks down the polling numbers on climate change. #CNN #News
title: Bill Gates & Americans on climate change: Harry Enten runs the numbers

author: CNN
description:
Hurricane Melissa made history as the strongest storm ever to strike Jamaica, and one of the most powerful Atlantic hurricanes on record. Fueled by abnormally hot sea water, the storm exploded in strength and tore across the island with 185 mph winds, rewriting the limits of what’s possible in the Caribbean.
#cnn #news
title: All the ways Melissa made records

author: CNN
description:
Millions of Americans could lose access to a crucial food assistance program in the coming weeks amid the federal government shutdown. Without SNAP benefits, people will have to decide whether to use their limited budgets to buy groceries, pay rent, fill prescriptions or turn on the heat.

CNN's Boris Sanchez and Brianna Keilar speak with Kasey McBlais, a mother and SNAP recipient concerned about losing benefits, and Joel Berg, CEO of Hunger Free America. #CNN #News
title: Millions of Americans may lose food assistance Saturday

author: CNN
description: The Federal Reserve on Wednesday lowered interest rates for the second time this year in a continued bid to prevent unemployment from surging.  CNN's Matt Egan and Richard Quest report. #CNN #News
title: Fed cuts rates for second-straight time to lowest level in three years

author: CNN
description: The White House fired six members of an independent federal agency charged with advising the president, Congress and Washington, DC, on design and aesthetics, according to a source familiar with the matter. CNN's Alayna Treene reports.
title: The White House fires six members of Commission of Fine Arts

author: CNN
description: On La Dolce Vita Orient Express, there is one staff member for every two passengers on board. The luxury experience just opened in Italy and CNN went behind the scenes to see how it all rumbles along smoothly. For more on this and other train journeys, head to cnn.com/travel #cnn #news #travel
title: The Orient Express, a 150-year-old idea, returns to Italy

author: CNN
description: Two suspects arrested in connection with the theft of France’s crown jewels from the Louvre museum have admitted involvement in the heist and have been remanded in custody, the Paris prosecutor’s office said on Wednesday. The Paris prosecutor also said the stolen jewels are not in the authorities’ possession.   #CNN #News
title: Prosecutor says Louvre heist jewelry has not been recovered despite arrests

author: CNN
description: John King speaks to voters across all five of New York City's boroughs on the eve of what could be a historic choice for mayor. It's the city that launched President Donald Trump. Is it about to elect the anti-Trump? #CNN #News
title: Race for mayor: NYC’s message to the world

description: Hurricane Melissa made landfall in Cuba as a Category 3 storm. CNN's Patrick Oppmann shows some of the damage that he can see in Santiago de Cuba. #CNN #News

description: Premiums for Affordable Care Act coverage will skyrocket 26%, on average, next year, according to a KFF analysis released Tuesday evening, just days before open enrollment starts on November 1. CNN’s Tami Luhby reports. #CNN #News
title: Obamacare enrollees get first look at 2026 prices as premiums soar

description:
Jamaica’s national police are clearing roads and removing downed trees after Hurricane Melissa tore across the island. Communities are grappling with widespread flooding, debris and power outages in the storm’s aftermath.
#cnn #news

description: At least five homes have collapsed into the Atlantic in Buxton, North Carolina. It's the second time in a month that hurricane-driven tides have swallowed houses along this stretch of coast. #cnn #buxton #northcarolina

description: BTS’s RM thanked his bandmates and fans at the APEC CEO Summit in South Korea. He also urged world leaders to support artists and the creative industry around the world. #CNN #News #BTS

description: Category 3 Hurricane Melissa has made landfall in Cuba after devastating Jamaica. The storm brings with it maximum sustained winds of 120 mph, according to the National Hurricane Center, and rainfall of between 10 to 20 inches. #cnn #cuba #hurricanemelissa

author: CNN
description: President Donald Trump received a replica of a historic golden crown from South Korean president Lee Jae Myung. The gold-plated gift, decorated with trees and animals, is based on the ancient Silla Kingdom’s gold crown. At the ceremony in Gyeongju, South Korea, Trump was also awarded South Korea’s highest honor, the Grand Order of Mugunghwa. CNN’s Will Ripley reports. #CNN #News #SouthKorea
title: Trump gets gold crown from South Korea

author: CNN
description: Elkhorn and staghorn corals are now “functionally extinct” in Florida's reef system after record-breaking ocean temperatures, according to a study led by the National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration’s Coral Reef Watch and Chicago’s Shedd Aquarium.
title: Critical Florida corals now 'functionally extinct'

description:
Luke Bryan is one of country music’s biggest stars. He's also faced great loss. In this personal and revealing conversation with Anderson, Luke shares how faith, family, and music have helped him "do what you do to get through." 

Join the community to share your story and watch Anderson's weekly streaming show All There Is Live at https://cnn.com/allthereis

description: At least 64 people have died in a massive police raid aimed at organized crime in Rio de Janeiro on Tuesday, security officials told CNN Brasil. title: Largest ever police raid in Brazil's favela leaves at least 64 dead

author: CNN
description:
Hurricane Melissa swept through the Caribbean, hitting Jamaica and causing significant damage. Jamaica's Prime Minister told CNN's Anderson Cooper there "would be devastating impacts" wherever the eye of Hurricane Melissa hit the island. The storm continues to lose some strength, but remains a very dangerous hurricane as it heads towards Cuba.

0:00 CNN meteorologist Derek Van Dam reports from Kingston, Jamaica

8:52 CNN international correspondent Patrick Oppmann reports from Santiago, Cuba
11:50 Jake Tapper speaks with Debra Shields, a tourist stranded in Lucea, Jamaica

17:56 CNN chief climate correspondent Bill Weir reports

title: 'This storm is a monster': CNN meteorologist on Hurricane Melissa hitting Jamaica
